Algorithm
Initialize the graph with edge costs and heuristic values.
Create an OPEN list (priority queue) and a CLOSED set.
Insert the source node into the OPEN list with:
g(n)=0
f(n)=g(n)+h(n)
Repeat until the OPEN list is empty:
Remove the node with the lowest f(n).
If the node is the goal, stop.
Otherwise, add it to the CLOSED set.
For each neighboring node:

Calculate the new path cost:

g(neighbor)=g(current)+edge cost

Compute:

f(neighbor)=g(neighbor)+h(neighbor)
If this path is better than the previous one, update the cost and parent.
Insert the neighbor into the OPEN list.
Trace back from the goal to the source using the parent dictionary.
Display the optimal path and total path cost.
